The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Gold jewellery worth over Rs 1 lakh, adorning a Jagadhatri idol in in Howrahs Andul, were stolen early on Tuesday. Residents of Vivekananda Nagar said they were at the pandal till 3am. The jewellery were missing when they returned in the morning. Puja committee members and residents blocked Andul Road for half an hour in the morning, demanding that police recover the jewellery and arrest the culprits.    Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will inaugurate Nibedita Bhavan, the new office of the West Bengal Board of Secondary Education, in Salt Lake on Thursday.    An eight-year-old boy was rescued from his employers fast food shop at Muchipara, where he had been held captive for over 12 hours, on Tuesday afternoon. Shop-owner Vinod Sonkar, against whom a case of wrongful confinement has been registered, is absconding. Police raided the shop after residents reported that Moinuddin Gazi had been kept confined there.     Railway Board chairman Vivek Sahay on Tuesday inspected the Noapara maintenance base of Metro Railway. He announced a reward of Rs 50,000 for the employees for maintaining it properly and keeping it clean, said an official.    A fire broke out in a four-storey shoe-manufacturing unit in Topsia around 9.30am on Tuesday. Four tenders brought the blaze under control in an hour. No one was injured. Fire officers said the flames had spread quickly as inflammable adhesives were stored in the building.   fire broke out on the fifth floor of Yogayog Bhavan on CR Avenue. Employees doused the flames before fire brigade turned up.    The driver of a Maruti van was injured when the vehicle collided with a truck on Vidyasagar Setu on Tuesday evening. The truck sped away. Zahirul Islam, 25, was treated at SSKM Hospital.    The 12th international conference on Frontiers in Handwriting Recognition, organised by the ISI, started on Tuesday.                                                                                                                                                  
